programa_resumido:
In this course, students apply design thinking and user centered design approaches throughout the course in order to develop a working prototype. There is a strong focus on advanced prototyping.

This discipline contributes to the development of the following course competencies:
Competency 1 – Analyze physical phenomena with the aid of models
Competency 3 – Manage the implementation of engineering solutions
Competency 6 – Research, innovate, and entrepreneurship

And the following related skills:
402. Understand and apply techniques for designing products, services, and businesses;
502. Design and make feasible the production of products, services, and businesses;
409-509. Understand the concepts and methods of project management to plan, execute, and control engineering and management projects;
205-504. Understand and apply the fundamentals of engineering (mechanical, chemical, electrical, structures, and materials) in solving engineering and management problems.
